Greetings all,

Andreas Tille, on 2024-11-30:
> I'd like to invite everybody to do join our advent calendar bug
> squashing party.  Its fun ... and if you need help to fix some bug just
> raise your question on Matrix or here on the list.

Count me in!  :)

> For those who want to squash bugs I recommend the following
> resources:
>
>  1. Classical BTS:
>      https://bugs.debian.org/debian-med-packaging@lists.alioth.debian.org
>     Please note that at the end is a list of "Forwarded bugs" which also
>     might need fixing.

If people look at the page, there are several bugs labelled
"Python SyntaxWarning", they are good both for newcomers to get
on tracks and for seasoned developpers who might want some
warmup.  It would be nice to have all those resolved before
trixie release.

We also have a sprawl of "Fails to build source after successful
build" from last year if we were to run out of Python syntax
warnings.  Those are usually low hanging fruits once one set up
one's workflow to reproduce the double build errors.  See the
wiki[1] to easily reproduce the issue with your workflow.

[1]: https://wiki.debian.org/qa.debian.org/FTBFS/DoubleBuild

> Any contribution to increase the quality of our packages is really
> welcome.  As promised earlier I will join this effort despite my
> DPL-"vacation" from Debian Med team.

Have a nice Advent period,  :)
